/`[Extensions]` sections in yellow. Context and skills are discovered from both project-local sources (`AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, `.claude/skills/*`, `.codex/skills/*`, `.agents/skills/*`) and user-hom
e globals (`~/.claude/CLAUDE.md`, `~/.claude/skills/*`, `~/.codex/skills/*`, `~/.pipy/skills/*`) so the section listing matches what Pi shows when global resources are present. Chrome rendering is sha
red between the no-tool and bounded tool-loop sessions through `pipy_harness.native.chrome`. |[0m
